      "justification": "The exact agreement for \\(m_s\\) depends on evaluating the running mass at a scale built from the same lepton masses used to define \\(\\mathcal F\\). This is not shown to arise from the underlying \\(A_4\\) framework, nor is robustness to nearby scale choices quantified. Since quark masses run with scale, this choice can materially affect the level of agreement and therefore the headline conclusion."
